The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, August 06, 2004 				 Teacher thrashed for slapping
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Krishnagar, Aug. 5: The father of a 10-year-old girl beat up a schoolteacher yesterday because he slapped her for not doing homework.																								Sanjoy Haldar, an English teacher at Matiari Junior High School at Nadias Kaligunj, about 140 km from Calcutta, was attacked at a marketplace.																								Priyanka Barman returned home crying and complained that she was slapped in school. Her father Prasenjit and grandfather started looking for the teacher immediately. 																								Haldar said: I tried to tell them that the slapping was necessary because not doing home work for three days in a row was a grave offence. But they just wouldnt listen.																								They threw the teacher to the ground and punched and kicked him. Others in the market rescued Haldar. 																								Police said the father-son duo is absconding.
